    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The current plan is to expose a tar stream from the HTTP API, leading to something like:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ swarm down | tar -x -C some/dir\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis then delegates things like preserving on-disk file permissions to `tar`, and you can then also just use `curl`:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ curl -H \"Accept: application/x-tar\" <gateway>/bzz:/<manifest> | tar -x -C some/dir\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe need to do some prerequisite work to add more file metadata to manifest entries (i.e. size, timestamps etc.).\r\n\r\nWe should also consider accepting a tar stream as a way to upload directory trees, for example:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ tar -c -C some/dir | curl -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/x-tar\" --data-binary @- <gateway>/bzzr:/\r\n```",
